cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Performance Benchmarking Experiment
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment designed to benchmark the performance
  of QUIC protocol implementations under varying network conditions. The methodology
  involved establishing a controlled environment on nodes tartu and tallinn, utilizing
  automated scripts for system configuration and build processes. Measurements focused
  on goodput (throughput) and execution time, captured through server and client logs
  analyzed by a Python evaluation script. The experiment utilized multiple configurations
  of bandwidth limits and QUIC implementations to assess protocol performance characteristics.
  Evaluation outputs include aggregated metrics and visualizations generated from
  the collected data.
